        public Setter(@NonNull
              String name,
              @NonNull
              String type,
              @NullAllowed
              String defaultValue,
              @NonNull
              String varName,
              boolean optional)
        The only way how to create setter.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the setter. For instance "setA"
        type - the type of the setter. For instance "int"
        defaultValue - the default value. Might be null. For instance "1".
        varName - the name of the variable. For instance "a".
        optional - true if the setter is optional in case, that argument is the same as default value.
